subSubSection.paragraph:
Despite an improvement in water quality due to remediation measures earlier this century (see
Dean et al. 2013
) water and sediment analysis from the UK sites all showed a high degree of contamination by the metals copper, zinc, iron and manganese. Concentrations of all metals exceeded standards and guidelines for both sediments and water (e.g.
Abdullah & Royle 1972
;
Warren 1981
; MacDonald et al. 2000 ;
Irish EPA 2001
). However, the water at all sites is slightly acid to near-neutral ( pH 5.8–7.3 ) which allows colonization by
M. nebulosa
. In Bulgaria the species was found in a locality characterized by municipal contamination only. The somatic rearrangements described here can thus be used as biomarkers for contaminants in water basins (
Michailova et al. 2012
), including trace metals and organic pollutants.
